(342, 1, '2019-12-10 11:08:57', '2019-12-10 11:08:57', 'Hyderabad for the third year in a row has emerged as the best city in terms of living standards among Indian cities, while Vienna has been ranked at the top globally in a list by consultancy firm Mercer.\n\nThe National Capital for the second straight year hit the lowest score among Indian cities for living standards, as per the Mercer\'s Quality of Living rankings 2017. Both Hyderabad and Pune ranked higher for quality of living than the country\'s traditional business centres Mumbai and New Delhi, which have been ranked at 154 and 161, respectively, by the report.\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div id=\"div-gpt-ad-1522301765091-0\" data-google-query-id=\"CLGVmJ73quYCFakUtwAdaQcAtQ\">\n<ol>\n 	<li>The nearly-awesome climate compared to North India.</li>\n 	<li>Blazing fast Beam internet. Enough said!</li>\n 	<li>Being a girl, you can walk out alone after dark and not be scared.</li>\n 	<li>The warmth of people here. The Telugu speaking crowd do not shy from speaking in broken Hindi just to make you comfortable.</li>\n 	<li>Cost of living and food here is less compared to other metros.</li>\n 	<li>Less traffic during rush hours compared to other metros.</li>\n 	<li>A perfect amalgation of the old and the new.</li>\n 	<li>I love the food here!</li>\n 	<li>If you have a lot of friends in IT sector, you\'re in luck coz everyone lives in the same 20 km area. Unlike in other cities you don\'t need to spend hours getting to their house.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Tortor neque adpiscing diam', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-12-10 11:08:57', '2019-12-10 11:08:57', '', 60, 'http://localhost/myblog/2019/12/10/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
